            <name>Guidance</name>
            <fieldText>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why do we share wins?&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The goal is to highlight the &quot;Adyen Way of Selling&quot; and &quot;Adyen Way of AM&quot; and to celebrate our successes together.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Have a win you&apos;d like to share?&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Tell the story highlighting the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://hub.is.adyen.com/commercial/strategy/adyen-way-of-selling/&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Adyen Way of Selling&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and/or&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://hub.is.adyen.com/our-company/organization/functions/account-management/&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Adyen Way of AM&lt;/a&gt;. Be sure to include relevant background (situation, pain points, impact), why the customer went with Adyen and if there were competitors involved, and any tactics used or lessons learned along the way.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What types of stories should be shared?&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Story submissions don&apos;t have to be limited to high-margin wins only. A story could highlight something weâ€™ve been working on for years, working together across teams to win, in-person meetings that led to a win, volume growth, etc.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How are these stories used?&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Some wins may be called out during the global or regional monthly updates, or used for the Sales Event, but teams have been asked to confirm with the AM/Sales Manager first.&lt;/p&gt;</fieldText>
